(
<figureCitation box="[201,301,461,485]" captionStart-0="Figure 4" captionStart-1="Figure 5" captionStart-2="Figure 6" captionStartId-0="7.[192,275,1848,1870]" captionStartId-1="11.[192,275,1391,1413]" captionStartId-2="13.[192,275,1907,1929]" captionTargetBox-0="[199,1422,703,1813]" captionTargetBox-1="[223,1434,212,1359]" captionTargetBox-2="[230,1401,1333,1873]" captionTargetId-0="figure@7.[192,1441,685,1817]" captionTargetId-1="figure@11.[192,1440,195,1379]" captionTargetId-2="figure@13.[230,1401,1333,1873]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionTargetPageId-2="13" captionText-0="Figure 4. Luctithonus Lingafelter, new genus. a) Head, anterior view. b) Antennal scape. c) Elytron showing location of basal crest. d) Hind tibia and tarsus. e) Anterior view of elytra showing location and extent of tufts. f) Prosternum and mesosternum. g) Pronotum." captionText-1="Figure 5. Luctithonus species. a) L. aski Lingafelter, new species, holotype male. b) L. aski Lingafelter, new species, paratype female. c) L. pantherinus (Zayas), d) L. pantherinus (Zayas), holotype male. e) L. duartensis Lingafelter, new species, holotype male, dorsal. f) L. duartensis Lingafelter, new species, paratype female, ventral. g) L. duartensis Lingafelter, new species, paratype female, ventral view of sternites." captionText-2="Figure 6. Distribution map of Luctithonus species known from Hispaniola." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703011" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703013" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3703015" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3703011/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3703013/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3703015/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 4–6</figureCitation>
